HEADWORD: full-term
<hw>full-term</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Gestated for the entire duration
of normal pregnancy; <as>as, a healthy <ex>full-term</ex> baby</as>; --
of new-born infants. Opposite of <ant>premature</ant>.</def> <see>Also
See: <er>mature</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

